strings: <voice_0x01000900><se_low>Yangus: Wot the...!?
<voice_0x01000901><se_low>Yangus: This ain't good, guv! Come on!
<voice_0x01000902><se_low>Yangus: Look lively!
<voice_0x01000903><se_low>*: Urgh! It looked at me!
<voice_0x01000904><se_high>*: Ewwww! It's hideous!

<voice_0x01000905><se_def>*: Get out! Get out, monster!
You're not welcome here!
<voice_0x01000906><se_def>*: Aaargh! Waaargh! Aaargh!

<voice_0x01000907><se_def>*: Get out! Out out out out!
*: Get out of 'ere!
*: We don't want your kind 'ere!
<voice_0x01000908><se_low>King Trode: Well! That was a fine reception!
<voice_0x01000909><se_low>King Trode: Don't they realise who I am!?

<voice_0x0100090A><se_low>King Trode: Hmph! Judging a book by its cover!
Don't they know it's what's inside that counts!?
<voice_0x0100090B><se_low>Yangus: Yeah! You can say that again!
<voice_0x0100090C><se_low>King Trode: So then, <hero>, did you manage to find Master Rylus?

<voice_0x0100090D><se_low>King Trode: What!? He's dead!?
Oh, no, no, no...

<voice_0x0100090E><se_low>King Trode: Well...
I suppose there's no point crying over spilt milk...

<voice_0x0100090F><se_low>King Trode: It's Dhoulmagus we're after! He's the one
who cursed the Princess and I, after all.
He's the one who made us look so ridiculous!

<voice_0x01000910><se_low>King Trode: I had hoped Rylus might be able to help us
locate him.
<voice_0x01000911><se_low>King Trode: But it seems we'll just have to track Dhoulmagus down by ourselves.
<voice_0x01000912><se_low>King Trode: With Rylus gone, we have nothing further to gain from staying here. Let's be on our way!
<voice_0x01000913><se_high>*: Wait!
<voice_0x01000914><se_high>*: Please...wait...
<voice_0x01000915><se_high>*: I'm sorry to come running after you like this. It's just that...I wanted to ask you a favour.
<voice_0x01000916><se_low>King Trode: Are you not afraid of me, young lady?
<voice_0x01000917><se_high>*: I dreamt about you...
<voice_0x01000918><se_high>*: I dreamt that some people came to town with a strange creature. It was...sort of halfway between a human and a monster...
<voice_0x01000919><se_high>*: And I dreamt that they could make wishes come true...

<voice_0x0100091A><se_low>King Trode: A strange creature!?
Are you referring to me?

<voice_0x0100091B><se_high>*: I'm so sorry!
I didn't mean to be rude!

<voice_0x0100091C><se_low>King Trode: Heh, not to worry. I've had worse things said
to me today! You know, you remind me of my Medea. You're about the same age.

<voice_0x0100091D><se_low>King Trode: Anyway, you say you had a dream about me?
Most peculiar...
<voice_0x0100091E><se_high>*: I'm sorry...

<voice_0x0100091F><se_high>*: I haven't even introduced myself.
I'm Valentina, daughter of the great fortune-
teller, Kalderasha.

<voice_0x01000920><se_high>Valentina: If you could just come to my house,
I'll explain everything there.

<voice_0x01000921><se_high>Valentina: It's by the well, at the far end of town.
I'll be waiting for you!

<voice_0x01000922><se_low>Yangus: Wot was she rabbitin' on about?
Come round my 'ouse, she says...
<voice_0x01000923><se_low>King Trode: Magnificent!

<voice_0x01000924><se_low>King Trode: She wasn't afraid to look at me at all!
Not one bit! Ah, she reminds me of my Medea!
<voice_0x01000925><se_low>King Trode: We must give this young girl a helping hand!

<voice_0x01000926><se_low>King Trode: Right then, <hero>, my boy!
Go and find the house by the well
and see what it is she wants.

<voice_0x01000927><se_low>King Trode: Hm? Me? I'll wait here with the Princess.
We don't want to cause any more of a stir.

<voice_0x01000928><se_low>King Trode: Hm? Am I to take it by the look on your face
that you haven't been to see that delightful
young girl yet?
<voice_0x01000929><se_low>King Trode: She said she lives in the house in front of the well. We'll be waiting here, so you hurry up and find out what it is she wants. Go on! Chop chop!
